Color. The alcohol-preserved holotype is mottled gray (near Grayish Horn Color, 91 ;
Smithe 1975
) on the dorsal side of the carapace. The walking legs are greenish-grey (near Grayish Horn Color, 91 ) dorsally, light gray (near Drab-Gray, 119 D) ventrally. The chelae are gray (near Drab Gray, 119 D) dorsally, light gray (near Light Drab, 119 C) ventrally. The ventral surface of the carapace is yellow-brown (near Buff, 124 ).
